Happy Friday friends!
Sitting at a cafe this morning and the couple next to me spilled their entire drink.
What happened next told me everything.
He got mad. She shut down. The whole energy at the table shifted and spread to the cafe. Date ruined over a spilled drink.
And I mean this genuinely: you can tell a lot about a person by how they respond to moments like that. How you handle the small stuff reveals how you handle the big stuff. It shows what you've worked through, reveals certain patterns, and can give you clues of quality of life.
Because here's the other option when the drink spills.
You laugh. You look at each other and go "well, there we go." You flag down the waiter, clean it up, and get back to your date. Ten minutes later it's a funny story instead of a ruined morning.
It’s all of our first time on earth (in this form) so let’s cut each other some slack.
The spilled drink is never really about the spilled drink.
It's about the gap between what happens and how you respond. That gap is everything. That gap is the work we are here to do!!
Don't cry over spilled milk (or coffee). Laugh, clean it up, and keep going.
First timer here too,
Joshua "Laughing All The Way" Church


